headline: Cboe Global Markets Declares Fourth-Quarter 2025 Dividend
summary: Cboe Global Markets, Inc. (Cboe: CBOE), the world's leading derivatives and securities exchange network, today announced its Board of Directors has declared a quarterly cash dividend of $0.72 per share of common stock for the fourth quarter of 2025. The fourth-quarter 2025 dividend is payable on December 15, 2025, to stockholders of record as of November 28, 2025.

headline: Tuttle Capital Management Launches First-Ever 0DTE Covered Call ETF on Strategy
summary: Greenwich, Connecticut--(Newsfile Corp. - October 23, 2025) - Tuttle Capital Management, a pioneer in innovative thematic and options-based ETFs, today announced the launch of the industry's first 0 Days to Expiration (0DTE) Covered Call ETF on Strategy. The Tuttle Capital MSTR 0DTE Covered Call ETF (CBOE: MSTK) seeks to deliver income and capital appreciation while addressing the risks of overnight market moves.MSTK is available today on the CBOE — learn more at IncomeBlastETFs.com.A Different.

headline: Tradr Debuts Leveraged ETFs on BLSH, DASH, FLY, IREN, NEM, OPEN, QS, SRPT & WULF
summary: Tradr ETFs, a provider of ETFs designed for sophisticated investors and professional traders, today launched nine new single stock leveraged ETFs, seven of which are first-to-market strategies. The funds, all listed on Cboe, seek to deliver twice (200%) the daily performance of a specific underlying stock.

headline: Should Cboe Global Markets’ (CBOE) Proposal for Extended Options Trading Hours Spur Investor Action?
summary: Cboe Global Markets recently filed a proposal with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission to extend trading hours for select equity options, introducing both pre-market and post-market sessions that would better align with the trading hours of underlying equities. This initiative marks a move toward nearly 24-hour access for options trading, increasing flexibility for investors and potentially changing market participation patterns if approved.
